@@TJvCustomOutlookBar
Summary
  TJvCustomOutlookBar is the base class for a control that displays pages and buttons in the style of the
  button bar in Microsoft(R) Outlook (R).
Description
  Use TJvCustomOutlookBar as a base class when defining a control that should contain a series of pages which
  in turn has buttons in a list in the style of Microsoft Outlook.

  Do not create instances of TJvCustomOutlookBar. To put an outlook bar on a form,
  use a descendant of TJvCustomOutlookBar, such as <LINK TJvOutlookBar>.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.ActivePage
Summary
  Specifies the page currently displayed by the control.
Description
  Read ActivePage to determine which page is selected by the user. The
  user selects a page by clicking the mouse on its button.
  ActivePage is readonly and cannot be used to change the currently active page.
  To change the active page or determine the active page by index, use ActivePageIndex instead.
See Also
  ActivePageIndex
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.ActivePageIndex
Summary
  Specifies the page currently displayed by the control.
Description
  Use ActivePageIndex to get or set the active page by index rather than by object.
  The value of ActivePageIndex identifies a page in the Pages property array.
  Changing the value of ActivePageIndex changes the ActivePage property.

  If there is no active page, reading ActivePageIndex gives a value of –1.

  Setting ActivePageIndex to a value that is out of bounds (less than 0 or greater than Pages.Count - 1)
  results in the control not changing the active page.
See Also
  ActivePage
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.BorderStyle
Summary
  Determines whether the control has a single line border around the client area or a flat style.
Description
  Use BorderStyle to affect the sharpness with which the client area of the control stands out.
  BorderStyle can have a value of either bsSingle or bsNone.
  If BorderStyle is bsSingle, the control has a single-line border around the client area.
  If BorderStyle is bsNone, there will be a flat style border.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.ButtonSize
Summary
  Specifies the size and look of the buttons on the pages.
Description
  Use ButtonSize to determine the current default size of buttons on a page. Change ButtonSize to
  change the button sizes of all pages in the outlook bar. Only pages having their
  <LINK TJvOutlookBarPage.ParentButtonSize,ParentButtonSize> property set to true will be affected.
See Also
  TJvOutlookBarPage.ParentButtonSize
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.Color
Summary
  Specifies the background color of the control.
Description
  Use Color to read or change the background color of the control.

  If a control's ParentColor property is true, then changing the Color
  property of the control's parent automatically changes the Color property
  of the control. When the value of the Color property is changed,
  the control's ParentColor property is automatically set to false.
See Also
  TControl.ParentColor
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.Font
Summary
  \Controls the attributes of text written on or in the control.
Description
  To change to a new font, specify a new TFont object.
  To modify a font, change the value of the Charset, Color, Height, Name, Pitch, Size, or Style of the TFont object.
  If a control's ParentFont property is true, then changing the Font
  property of the control's parent automatically changes the Font property
  of the control. When the value of the Font property is changed,
  the control's ParentFont property is automatically set to false.
See Also
  TControl.ParentFont
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.GetButtonAtPos
Summary
  Returns the button in the control indicated by the coordinates of a point on the control.
Description
  Call GetButtonAtPos to retrieve the button located at the coordinates given by P. If no button encloses the P.X and P.Y
  coordinates, nil is returned. This function can only return a button in the visible part of the active page.
Parameters
  P - a point in the control in window coordinates that should be enclosed by a button rectangle.
Return value
  The button at P or nil if no button is located at P.
See Also
  <LINK GetPageButtonAtPos>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.GetPageButtonAtPos
Summary
  Returns the page button (the button at the top of the page) in the control indicated by the coordinates
  of a point on the control.
Description
  Call GetPageButtonAtPos to retrieve the page button located at the coordinates given by P. If no page button encloses
  the P.X and P.Y coordinates, nil is returned.
Parameters
  P - a point in the control in window coordinates that should be enclosed by a page button rectangle
Return value
  The page button at P or nil if no page button is located at P
See Also
  <LINK GetButtonAtPos>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.LargeImages
Summary
  Provides a list of icon images to display for each button when ButtonSize is set to olbsLarge.
Description
  Set LargeImages to specify the bitmaps that should be
  displayed in the buttons when ButtonSize is olbsLarge. Each button on a page
  can be associated with a bitmap in this image list by setting its ImageIndex property.
See Also
  SmallImages, ButtonSize
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.OnButtonClick
Summary
  Occurs when the user clicks a button using the left mouse button.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnButtonClick event to take specific action when the user clicks a button. The clicked
  button is always located on the active page.
Parameters
  Sender - the object that triggered the event
  Index  - the index of the button that was clicked. The button is always located on the currently active page.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.OnEditButton
Summary
  Occurs when the user has changed the text of a button.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnEditButton event to take specific action when the user has changed the
  caption of a button.
See Also
  EditCaption, OnEditPage
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.OnEditPage
Summary
  Occurs when the user has changed the text of a page button.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnEditPage event to take specific action when the user has changed the
  caption of a page button.
See Also
  OnEditButton
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.OnPageChange
Summary
  Occurs after the active page has changed.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnPageChange event to take specific actions when the user has changed to a new active page.
Parameters
  Sender - the object that triggered the event
  Index  - the index of the new active page
See Also
  OnPageChanging
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.OnPageChanging
Summary
  Occurs just before the active page is to be changed.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnPageChanging event to take specific actions before the currently active page is changed.
  For example, you can use this event to prevent the user from changing to another page.
Parameters
  Sender      - the object that triggered the event
  Index       - the page index of the page that is to be made active
  AllowChange - set this parameter to false to disallow changing to the new page.
See Also
  OnPageChange
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.PageButtonHeight
Summary
  Specifies the height of a page button.
Description
  Read PageButtonHeight to determine the height of the buttons on the pages. Change PageButtonHeight to modify
  the height of all page buttons.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.Pages
Summary
  Provides indexed access to the pages in the bar.
Description
  Use Pages to access individual pages in the bar. Valid values of the Index
  parameter are in the interval 0 to Pages.Count - 1.
See Also
  TJvOutlookBarPages.Count
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.PopUpObject
Summary
  Indicates the component that last displayed the popup menu in response to a right mouse click.
Description
  Read PopUpObject to determine which control is currently
  using the popup menu. Since the pages and button in the outlook bar isn't real components, reading
  PopupMenu.PopupComponent always returns the outlook bar control. To access the real object that activated the
  popup menu, use PopupObject instead.

  To determine what object displayed the popup, you should check it against the three possible values:
  <CODE>
    if (JvOutlookBar1.PopupObject is TJvOutlookBar) then
      HandleBarPopup
    else if (JvOutlookBar1.PopupObject is TJvOutlookBarPage) then
      HandlePagePopup
    else if (JvOutlookBar1.PopupObject is TJvOutlookBarButton) then
      HandleBarButton;
  </CODE>
See Also
  PopupMenu
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.SmallImages
Summary
  Provides a list of icon images to display for each button when ButtonSize is set to olbsSmall.
Description
  Set SmallImages to specify the bitmaps that should be
  displayed in the buttons when ButtonSize is olbsSmall. Each button on a page
  can be associated with a bitmap in this image list by setting its ImageIndex property.
See Also
  LargeImages, ButtonSize
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomOutlookBar.ThemedBackground
Summary
  Specifies whether to paint the background of the outlook bar themed.
Description
  Use ThemedBackground to specify whether to paint the background of the outlook bar themed or
  non themed. This only applies to themed applications on windows XP systems.
Note
  Only for delphi 7.
