@@TJvOutlookBarButton
Summary
  A button on an outlook page.
Description
  The buttons on the pages of a TJvOutlookBar are of type TJvOutlookBarButton. To add a button to a page
  at design time, double-click the outlook bar to open the OutlookBar Editor. To add a button at runtime,
  call the Add method of the Buttons property of the page where the page should be added.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarButton.Assign
Summary
  Copies the contents of another button.
Description
  Call Assign to copy the content of another button to this button. If Source is not a TJvOutlookBarButton or descendant,
  inherited Assign is called.
Parameters
  Source - The object to copy from
See Also
  AssignTo
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarButton.Caption
Summary
  Specifies the text on the button.
Description
  Read Caption to determine the text displayed on the button. Change the value of Caption to change the
  text on the button. To allow the user to change the Caption at runtime, call the EditCaption function.
See Also
  EditCaption
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarButton.EditCaption
Summary
  Activates runtime editing of the buttons text.
Description
  Call EditCaption if you want to allow the user to change the buttons text at runtime. EditCaption
  activates an inplace editor that the user can type into. When the user presses ENTER, the text on the
  button is updated with the new value. If the user presses Escape or clicks outside the button,
  the text is not changed.

  To be notified when the user has finished editing the caption, assign an event handler to the
  <LINK TJvOutlookBar.OnEditButton,OnEditButton> event.
See Also
  TJvOutlookBar.OnEditButton
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarButton.ImageIndex
Summary
  Specifies the image to display on the button.
Description
  ImageIndex is used to set the image to display on the button. Depending on the value of
  <LINK TJvOutlookBar.ButtonSize, ButtonSize> the button displays an image either from
  <LINK TJvOutlookBar.LargeImages, LargeImages> or from <LINK TJvOutlookBar.SmallImages, SmallImages>.
See Also
  TJvOutlookBar.ButtonSize, TJvOutlookBar.LargeImages, TJvOutlookBar.SmallImages
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarButtons
Summary
  Collection class that maintains a list of buttons.
Description
  TJvOutlookBarButtons is the class type of the <LINK TJvOutlookBarPage.Buttons,Buttons> property and
  maintains a list of buttons. Use the methods of the class to Add, Delete and Exchange buttons.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarButtons.Add
Summary
  Adds a new button to the end of the list.
Description
  Call Add to add a new button to the list of buttons.
Return value
  The newly added button.
See Also
  Insert, Delete, Items
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarButtons.Insert
Summary
  Adds a new button and places it at the specified index in the list.
Description
  Call \Insert to \add a new button to the list of buttons at a specific index.
Parameters
  Index - The index where the button should be inserted.
Return value
  The newly created button.
See Also
  Add, Delete, Items
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarButtons.Items
Summary
  Provides indexed access to the buttons in the list.
Description
  Use Items to get indexed access to the buttons in the list. To iterate over the buttons, use
  Items along with the Count property to determine the number of items. Since Items is the default
  property for TJvOutlookBarButtons, you can leave it out in code when you want to access the items.
  <AUTOLINK OFF>
  <CODE>
  JvOutlookBar1.Pages[0].Buttons.Items[0].Caption := 'OK';
  </CODE>
  Equivalent:
  <CODE>
  JvOutlookBar1.Pages[0].Buttons[0].Caption := 'OK';
  </CODE>
  <AUTOLINK ON>
See Also
  Add, Delete, Count
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPage
Summary
  Represents a page on an outlook bar control.
Description
  TJvOutlookBarPage represents a page on a TJvOutlookBar control. Do not create instances of this class yourself.
  Instances are created and maintained by TJvOutlookBarPages as needed.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPage.Alignment
Summary
  Determines how text is aligned within the page button.
Description
  Use Alignment to change the way the text is formatted by the page button.
Note
  This property is not implemented yet.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPage.Buttons
Summary
  Provides indexed access to the buttons in the list.
Description
  Use Buttons to access the buttons on a page using an index. Valid indices are between 0 and
  Buttons.Count - 1.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPage.ButtonSize
Summary
  Specifies the button size used on the page.
Description
  Use ButtonSize to specify how buttons are displayed and where they retrieve their images from.
  If ButtonSize is olbsSmall, images are displayed to the left of the button's Caption, if
  ButtonSize is olbsLarge, images are displayed above the text, centered on the button.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPage.Caption
Summary
  Specifies the text on the page button.
Description
  Set Caption to change the text on the page button. \Read Caption to determine the current text on the
  page button.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPage.Color
Summary
  Specifies the background color of the page.
Description
  Use Color to read or change the background color of the control.
See Also
  ParentColor, Font, ParentFont
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPage.EditCaption
Summary
  Activates runtime editing of the page button's text.
Description
  Call EditCaption if you want to allow the user to change the page button's text at runtime. EditCaption
  activates an inplace editor that the user can type into. When the user presses ENTER, the text on the page
  button is updated with the new value. If the user presses Escape or clicks outside the page button, the text is not changed.

  To be notified when the user has finished editing the caption, assign an event handler to the OnEditPage event.
See Also
  OnEditPage, TJvOutlookBar.EditCaption
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPage.Font
Summary
  Specifies the font to use when writing text on the page button.
Description
  Set Font to specify the font to use for writing text on the page button. The value of Font is a
  TFont object. Set the properties of the TFont object to specify the font face, color, size, style,
  and any other aspects of the font.
See Also
  Color, ParentFont, ParentColor
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPage.Image
Summary
  Specifies a background image for the page
Description
  Use Image to specify an image to use as a background for the page. If an image is assigned, it
  is automatically tiled to fill the entire ClientRect of the page.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPage.ImageIndex
Summary
  Specifies the image to display on the page button.
Description
  Read ImageIndex to determine the image displayed on the page. Change ImageIndex to display another image.
  To remove an image, set ImageIndex to -1.
Note
  This property is not yet implemented.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPage.ParentButtonSize
Summary
  Determines where a page looks for its button size information.
Description
  To have a page use the same button size as its parent control, set ParentButtonSize
  to true. When the value of the page's ButtonSize property changes, ParentButtonSize is
  set to false automatically.
See Also
  ButtonSize
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPage.ParentColor
Summary
  Determines where a control looks for its color information.
Description
  To have a control use the same color as its parent control, set ParentColor to true. If ParentColor
  is false, the control uses its own Color property.

  When the value of a control's Color property changes, ParentColor becomes false automatically.
See Also
  ParentFont, ParentButtonSize
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPage.ParentFont
Summary
  Determines where a control looks for its font information.
Description
  To have a control use the same font as its parent control, set ParentFont
  to true. If ParentFont is false the control uses its own Font property.
  Set ParentFont to true for all controls in order to ensure
  that all the controls on a form have a uniform appearance. For example, if ParentFont
  is true for all controls in a form, changing the form’s Font property to 12-point Courier
  causes all controls on the form to use that font.

  When the value of a control's Font property changes, ParentFont becomes false automatically.
See Also
  Font, ParentColor, Color
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPage.TopButtonIndex
Summary
  Specifies the index of the first visible button on the page.
Description
  Read TopButtonIndex to determine the topmost visible button on the page. Change
  TopButtonIndex to make another button the topmost button on the page.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPages
Summary
  Maintains a list of outlook pages.
Description
  TJvOutlookBarPages is the type of the Items property of <LINK TJvOutlookbar>. TJvOutlookBarPages is derived
  from TCollection and maintains a list of TJvOutlookBarPage objects.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPages.Add
Summary
  Add a new page to the control.
Description
  Call add to add a new page to the outlook control.
Return value
  The newly created page.
See Also
  Insert, Delete, Items
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPages.Assign
Summary
  Copy the content of another TJvOutlookBarPages to this object.
Description
  Call Assign to copy the content of another TJvOutlookBarPages object to this object. If Source is
  a TJvOutlookBarPages, Assign clears all pages and buttons in this object and copies the pages and
  buttons from Source.
Parameters
  Source - The object to copy from.
See Also
  AssignTo
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPages.Insert
Summary
  Adds a new page to the list at a specific index.
Description
  Call Insert to add a new page to the list of pages at a specific index.
Parameters
  Index - The index where the page should be inserted.
Return value
  The newly created page.
See Also
  Add, Delete, Items
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookBarPages.Items
Summary
  Provides indexed access to the pages in the list.
Description
  Use Items to access the pages in the list using an index. The first page in the list is at index 0 and the
  last item is at \Count - 1.
See Also
  Count
